  (text "These novel bus protection circuits\nprevent traditional I2C/SPI failure \nmodes where a single slave failure\ncan disable the entire bus.\n\nLearn more: \nhttps://doi.org/10.36227/techrxiv.15166620\n\nBy default, slave clock and/or data lines \ncan be held low and the Master (SAMD51) \nwill still be able to communicate with the \nremainder of the bus.\n\nThey can individually be bypassed by \nremoving the transistor(s) and soldering\nthe 0ohm the jumpers below."
    (at 48.133 193.294 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.7526 1.7526)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid f6c7c86f-78c3-4925-a1d2-af8439a4bb73)
  )

